message.content: Enallagma civile is a species of damselfly belonging to the family Coenagrionidae. This species is commonly found in North America and its preferred habitats include ponds, swamps, and slow-moving streams. The Enallagma civile is a small damselfly, ranging from 23 to 34 millimeters in length, with a slender body and narrow wings. The males are blue with black markings, while the females have a brownish coloration with black markings. The eyes of Enallagma civile are large and prominent, with a metallic sheen in males. The species is active during the day and can be observed flying low over the water or perched on vegetation. The Enallagma civile is a important species in aquatic ecosystems as it plays an important role as a predator of small insects.
